This paper deals with text mining and machine learning techniques applied to a large corpus of neuroimaging research papers. The use of Deep Boltzmann Machines (DBMs) is a novel approach to this problem, and is likely to be of interest to researchers in the areas of natural language processing (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), and neural networks (cs.NE).
